{"questions":[{"mcqId":"11_math_ch3_q1","chapterId":"math_ch3","question":"The value of sin(31π/3) is:","options":["1/2","√3/2","-√3/2","1"],"correctIndex":1,"explanation":"sin(31π/3) = sin(10π + π/3) = sin(π/3) = √3/2.","ncertPage":65,"difficulty":"MEDIUM","subject":"Mathematics"},{"mcqId":"11_math_ch3_q2","chapterId":"math_ch3","question":"The radian measure of 40° 20' is:","options":["121π/540","121π/360","241π/1080","121π/270"],"correctIndex":1,"explanation":"40° 20' = 40 + 20/60 = 40 + 1/3 = 121/3 degrees. Radian measure = (121/3) * (π/180) = 121π/540.","ncertPage":54,"difficulty":"HARD","subject":"Mathematics"},{"mcqId":"11_math_ch3_q3","chapterId":"math_ch3","question":"If tan x = -5/12 and x lies in the second quadrant, then sin x is:","options":["5/13","12/13","-5/13","-12/13"],"correctIndex":1,"explanation":"In second quadrant, sin is positive. sec²x = 1 + tan²x = 1 + 25/144 = 169/144. cos x = -12/13 (negative in Q2). sin x = tan x * cos x = (-5/12) * (-12/13) = 5/13.","ncertPage":62,"difficulty":"MEDIUM","subject":"Mathematics"}]}